page.title: 17Social Events in Woodchurch
page.content: There are many different events in Woodchurch. On the Green every year there is a carnival. The carnival is a time of year when people get dressed up and go on floats and we all have fun. Once a year there is a Whizz Bang and Bonfire Night, when we have fireworks. The Whizz Bang raises money for the Windmill. Nearly every month there is a Church Parade. There is also the Royal Btitish Legion. Every week there is Sunday School, where people learn about God. On Fridays, there is the Darby and Joan club for old people. There is also a Library, Bingo and Mother and Toddlers club. There is also Brownies, Guides, Cubs and Scouts.
